Package com.sympos2.models

Class Obra

java.lang.Object
com.sympos2.models.Obra
public class Obra extends Object
This is the class to creates Obra objects, which represents Book and Article entities in database by the parameter: "tipo".

  • Constructor Details

    • Obra

      public Obra()

    • Obra

      public Obra(Long isbn, LocalDate fechaPublicacion, String titulo, String autor, String tipo, String abstracto, String lugar_publicacion, List<String> temas, String editorial)
      Constructor for Comentario as the type Book
      Parameters:
      isbn - Long which represents the id of the book.
      fechaPublicacion - LocalDate with the date of publication of the book.
      titulo - String with the title of the book.
      autor - String with the name of the book's author.
      tipo - String to determinate the type of the Obra, in this case probably will be "BOOK".
      abstracto - String with the resume of the book.
      lugar_publicacion - String with the place where the book was published, in this case a country or city
      temas - an ArrayList of Strings with the themes which the book could talk.
      editorial - String with the name of the editorial which published the book.

    • Obra

      public Obra(Long isbn, LocalDate fechaPublicacion, String titulo, String autor, String tipo, String abstracto, String lugar_publicacion, List<String> temas, String editorial, int paginaini, int paginafin)
      Constructor for Comentario as the type Article
      Parameters:
      isbn - Long which represents the id of the article.
      fechaPublicacion - LocalDate with the date of publication of the article.
      titulo - String with the title of the article.
      autor - String with the name of the article's author.
      tipo - String to determinate the type of the Obra, in this case probably will be "ARTICLE".
      abstracto - String with the resume of the article.
      lugar_publicacion - String with the place where the article was published, in this case a book or magazine.
      temas - an ArrayList of Strings with the themes which the article could talk.
      editorial - String with the name of the editorial which published the article or the book/magazine where the article was published.
